'''柳约翰''' 原名'''有俊'''<ref>{{cite journal |last=O'Neil |first=Robert M. |authorlink= |coauthors= |title=美国学术自由面临的新挑战 |journal=国际高等教育 |volume=2 |issue=4 |pages= |id= |url=http://gse.sjtu.edu.cn/jihe/vol2issue4/2.html |accessdate=2014-09-19 |quote= |date=2009年12月 |author= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304185548/http://gse.sjtu.edu.cn/jihe/vol2issue4/2.html |archive-date=2016-03-04 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>（'''{{lang-en|John Yoo}}'''，{{bd|1967年|7月10日|}}），[[韩裔美籍|韩裔美籍]]法律学者，现任美国[[加州大学伯克利分校|加州大学伯克利分校]]法学院教授，曾在[[小布什|小布什]]总统任内出任[[美国司法部|美国司法部]]高级官员，因其批准美国[[美国陆军|陆军]]与[[中央情报局|中央情报局]]在[[伊拉克战争|伊拉克战争]]中对[[战俘|战俘]]施行[[酷刑|暴力审讯]]（尤其是使用“[[坐水凳|坐水凳]]”方式）而饱受争议。<ref name="monster">{{cite news | url = http://www.esquire.com/features/john-yoo-0608 | title = Is John Yoo a Monster? | work = [[Esquire_(magazine)|Esquire]] | date = May 13, 2008 | accessdate = April 21, 2009 | first = John | last = Richardson | archive-date = 2009-05-02 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090502003300/http://www.esquire.com/features/john-yoo-0608 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/torture/interviews/yoo.html | publisher = [[Public_Broadcasting_Service|PBS]] | work = [[Frontline_(U.S._TV_series)|Frontline]] | title = Frontline Interview with John Yoo | date = July 19, 2005 | accessdate = 2014-09-19 | archive-date = 2021-01-25 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210125230450/https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/torture/interviews/yoo.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>

==生平==
柳约翰生於韩国[[漢城|漢城]]（後改名首爾），年少时同父母移民美国并定居[[费城|费城]]，1993年获得[[宾夕法尼亚州|宾夕法尼亚州]]律师从业资格，在加州大学伯克利分校法学院就任教授。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.padisciplinaryboard.org/pa_attorney_info.php?id=69500&pdcount=0 |title=PA Attorney Information John Choon Yoo |work=The Disciplinary Board of the Supreme Court of Pennsylvania |accessdate=July 8, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110930200148/http://www.padisciplinaryboard.org/pa_attorney_info.php?id=69500&pdcount=0 |archivedate=2011年9月30日 }}</ref><ref name="latimes" />

2001年，小布什政府聘请柳约翰就任副助理司法部长，任期中主持批准对美国[[反恐战争|反恐战争]]中俘获的战俘实施被外界普遍视作[[酷刑|酷刑]]的“加强审讯”，其中“[[坐水凳|坐水凳]]”一项尤其受到争议。柳约翰认为，美国施行的这些审讯手段不受到[[日内瓦公约|日内瓦公约]]中保护战俘权利条款的限制，同时布什政府批准这些审讯手段也不违反1996年颁布的《反战争罪法》。<ref>{{cite news |title=Holder tells Senators Waterboarding is Torture |first=David |last=Stout |date=15 January 2009 |accessdate=21 April 2009 |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/16/us/politics/16holdercnd.html?scp=3&sq=Eric%20Holder%20torture&st=cse |work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |archive-date=2019-12-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191219010425/https://www.nytimes.com/2009/01/16/us/politics/16holdercnd.html?scp=3&sq=Eric%20Holder%20torture&st=cse |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>[http://www.gwu.edu/~nsarchiv/NSAEBB/NSAEBB127/ "The Interrogation Documents: Debating U.S. Policy and Methods"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.gwu.edu/~nsarchiv/NSAEBB/NSAEBB127/ |date=20150320094325 }}, George Washington University;
